Subject:      Re: H. Chopin
Comments: cc: lolpoet@mailhub.acsu.buffalo.edu
 
Loss et alia -
 
Here's what I found out about the Henri Chopin CD:
 
It's called Les 9 Saintes-Phonies & it's released by Staalplaat in
conjunction with Korm Plastics.  I have the following addresses for
Staalplaat:
 
postbus 11453
1001 GL Amsterdam
The Netherlands
 
&
 
P O Box 83296
Oregon  97283
USA
 
 
Yes I realize that that doesn't include a city in Oregon, that's all I have.
 
The disc includes seven pieces from 1956 through the mid 1980s, with two
collaborations - one with Sten hanson & one with Larry Wendt.
 
I haven't heard the CD, but it should be available through any store that
carries "ambient/industrial" music, which is what Staalplaat mostly deals
in.  I can provide the address, phone, or e-mail for Wall of Sound in
Seattle, where I saw the disc, if anyone wants it.
 
Bests
 
 
 
Herb Levy
herb@eskimo.com
