From:         Joe Amato <amato@CHARLIE.ACC.IIT.EDU>
Subject:      Re: biographies...
 
kevin and ed, thanx for yr notes on reynolds' tome, very helpful in helping
to situate my own reading of same... as tenney n. knows (tenney, what do
*you* think?) i'm trying to figure out how to rework an essay begun long
ago in a class i took with don byrd, about how whitman's poetry operates
along the same conceptual coordinates as physicists who were at that time
busy articulating the 'conservation of energy'... never been successful in
drawing correspondences out to the satisfaction of the cultural studies
folks, the lit. crit. folks, OR the more science-bound folks... perhaps b/c
i haven't done enough with specifically economic factors (which related
discussion a number of weeks ago was for me enlightening)... but fact is
i'm really plying correspondences per se, and not all that focused on the
discursive machinery of the times... which is why i was hoping to use
reynolds' new work, if only by counterexample...
 
anyway, thanx again...
 
best,
 
joe
