Date:         Fri, 2 Feb 1996 07:27:25 -0800
Reply-To:     UB Poetics discussion group <POETICS@UBVM.CC.BUFFALO.EDU>
Sender:       UB Poetics discussion group <POETICS@UBVM.CC.BUFFALO.EDU>
From:         Kevin Killian <dbkk@SIRIUS.COM>
Subject:      The Hellfire Club
 
This is Kevin Killian speaking.  I've been reading Peter Straub's new
thriller, "The Hellfire Club."  In it, for reasons too complicated to
explain here, a serial killer on the run is forced to pose as a language
poet and gets put on the spot, asked where he's "been published."  In Avec,
Conjunctions and Lingo.  "Are you part of a community of poets?"  "We
Language poets like to get together at a nice little saloon called
Gilhoolie's."  "How would you define Language poetry?" "Exactly what it
sounds like," Dart said, "Language, as much of it as possible."
 
If any of you knows Peter Straub's address please send it to me
back-channel.  Thanks!
