recently as last year, is extremely ill. -- The following from a local paper:
 
"Higgins, 59, revealed last week that his health has deteriorated to the
point where he can do nothing but sit and wait for an available liver.
The operation would be performed at UCLA Medical Center.  Higgins and his
wife, Gina, are planning to raise the money needed for the procedure and
post-op care."
 
In addition to Higgins's remarkable work as a musician, he launched the
World Stage performance space and record label based in Leimert Park.
Last year his wife opened the California Coffee House in Culver City.
Neither of these will produce enough income for the operation.
 
