Chris,
 
You are hallucinating. Never in my life have I ever heard anybody who
has been described as a language poet "exclude" Bernadette. Please look
on page 410 of In the American Tree (and for the next 14 pages) and her
theoretical writing in the "Second Front" section of the anthology (p.
557), which comes immediately before my own. And I think that the
experience of _Tree_ is typical.
 
