From:         Ron Silliman <rsillima@IX.NETCOM.COM>
Subject:      Re: Pomo
 
I'm curious about the assumption behind Mark Nowak's no-doubt
well-intended comments about pomo and Pomo. Where precisely is it
written that homophones shall only have one denotation? Can you can the
can-can on such grounds?
 
The term pomo has been used for so long (popularized first I do believe
by Greg Tate in VLS in the late 80s) that there's been a comedy team in
San Francisco for several years that calls itself Pomo Afro Homo.
 
Ron Silliman
