Subject:      pomo-ra-ma
 
hear hear to ron to limit our vocabs in order to re-strict meaning to only
certain pre-scribed notions about what or how words mean is silly and an long
term effort to systematically erradicate the use of a word because it might
be offensive or derogatory or oppressive would in the end leave us with very
few words i admit that a word may be damaging culturally but there is no way
to get around that language is opressive the way in which we use language is
opressive the way in which language means is opressive so singling out pet
peeves tolambast seems to me a mis-guided attempt at a linguistic re-education
that is doomed to failure
 
wrh
