that we know right away what we're reading?
that there's no delay of assembly, no language
acquisition involved? I don't mean that
everything should be written in another language
but don't these puzzleworks get more (games?
mazes?) through when there's some question
of readability? "Y**r D**k" by Padgett or
"Prom in Toledo Night" by Ann Lauterbach
are two examples of nearly readable works
that develop and sustain.. what.. something
that continually is clear and eludes.. while
conveying puzzlingly strong affects
 
