Subject:      Larry Eigner: in memoriam
 
Two Eigner poems in memoriam of Larry:
 
 
This one was published in THE GERTRUDE STEIN AWARDS volume. Norma Cole
reminded me its appropriateness:
 
 
 
 
n o  m o r e  p o e t r y !
 
 
                but the window
 
                          I suddenly shifted positon and
 
                                really have to go
 
 
 
          N o w  a g a i n
 
 
 
          Mountain ice
 
                on the rocky path
                with the knockout view
                                  ---I watch my step
                                        in time
 
 
 
 
 
                                       *
 
 
 G o o d
 
 
     I've had the bagel and I've
                    eaten it too
 
 
 
 
 
 
FROM Eigner's forthcoming volume:  readiness / enough / depends / on
 
 
 
 
                 If life,
                         things,
                                weren't so
                                           intersting, it,
                                                          they,
                                                               would kill
                                                                         me
