From:         Tom Beard <beard@MET.CO.NZ>
Subject:      Re: neut gender
 
>a simpler idea--'e' (which could or could not be capitalized). this
>puts 3rd person on equal footing with 1st (and 2nd person just being a more
>complex spelling of another vowel, we have some consistency among the
>pronouns))
 
i.e.:
 
I, you, e,
I O U
E I E I O
 
 
 
 
        Tom Beard
 
