>Alan
 
 
 
There's a book called *A Primer for the Gradual Understanding of Gertrude
Stein*, by, I'm pretty sure, Gertrude Stein, in which she talks some about
revision in *Tender Buttons*. ("PEELED PENCIL, CHOKE" was originally a much
longer piece, etc.)  I skimmed it a couple of years ago & am not sure if it
addresses your other questions, but it might be worth taking a look at.
"How long it took" can probably be found somewhere in *Autobio of Alice B T*.
 
