Re: Marianne Moore:
 
William Carlos Williams told Moore that she was both in and out of place in the
bohemianism of Greenwich Village, and called her "a red berry hanging to a
jaded rosebush."
 
To this Miss Moore replied, "I cannot feel sorry for the red berry when the
bush is so full of sap."
 
 
--Nancy Dunlop   (SUNY Albany)
 
 
P.S.--"The Fish" is one of my Under-Pillow 10.
