Ryan -- It strikes me that there's something like a family resemblance between
Bernstein on poetry in "Artifice of Absorption" & Barthes on 19th-cent. prose
in "S/Z" & "Pleasure of the Text" especially.  And I think I do mean family re-
semblance, in the sense that Bernstein is building on/reacting to Veronica For-
rest-Thomson, who is coming straight out of Tel Quel (she published an essay on
Tel Quel poetics), i.e., straight out of Barthes' intellectual milieu -- possi-
bly staight out of Barthes' own seminar, though I'm not sure of that.
 
Brian McHale
