From:         Edward Foster <EFOSTER@VAXC.STEVENS-TECH.EDU>
Subject:      Re: The Nightable Ten
 
again, tho, i'd insist that "design" or "focus" is precisely what the
poetry, not the editor, must provide. the value of a troika (particularly
when they themselves have such radically different poetics) is that it
can undermine assumptions about "design." i think that if an anthology
has a "coherent menu," the editor may think the poems are "objects,"
arranged.
