Two forthcoming poetry readings in the NE of England:
 
Friday February 23rd at 8.00pm
MORDEN TOWER, Back Stowell Street, Newcastle upon Tyne
 
PETER RUSSELL
A rare visit to the UK from this elder-statesman-in-exile, who's lived in
Italy since the 50's. Russell edited NINE in the 50's, publishing Bunting
(when no-one else in Britain did) Pound and others. He now produces
MARGINALIA, a newsletter largely devoted to his own work, which has been
described as "a kind of high, literary underground".
 
Friday March 1st at 6.30pm
BASIL BUNTING POETRY CENTRE
Music School, Palace Green, Durham City
 
NICOLE BROSSARD / DAPHNE MARLATT // GERALDINE MONK / MAGGIE O'SULLIVAN
