From:         Rod Smith <AERIALEDGE@AOL.COM>
Subject:      Re: re re rewriting that Blasing
 
A book to read re Blasing is _The Grounding of American Poetry_ by Stephen
Fredman, deals with Black Mountain re the Transcendentalists & shows ways in
which "tradition" can be individually invented and generative. I.e. "take
what you need and leave the rest." Some excellent readings of Olson & Duncan
there. As to why I'm always dis-recommending Blasing _Cultural Capital_ by
John Guillory (as well as the Rasula) is where to start I think. Geeze, I
know too much about this stuff for somebody not in ackademe. (not that I know
all that much  ;)
--Rod
PS-- The Fredman is Cambridge hc only '93 or '94 around $45 (ouch). Cultural
Capital tho is U. Chicago pb.
