Jordan, thanks for correcting me about Lucy van Pelt.
I'm sure Uncle Wally kept her in furs,
even though she had to change her name.
 
Here's a short poem, for all you eye-blitzed people fed up with me.
The key to this poem is the letter ... S.
 
                      *
 
Time now for the trees to shroud the earth, time
when the wind dies down,
and over the still mirror
a faded voice is whispering.
 
Time again to climb into the old
music-box in the forest,
and wind the iron spring--
 
it is letter by letter,
line by line.
 
                      *
--HG
