From:         Chris Stroffolino <LS0796@CNSVAX.ALBANY.EDU>
Subject:      Re: (C) up for grabs
 
   Eryque---thanks for your reply, and i don't disagree with you perse
   (and if i get to teach again some day I may even teach full books by
    single poets---and yes even SUN AND MOON poets perhaps dug not to be GLIB!)
    but the point I was trying to make is different, and I still think
    maligned. It's the point that one poem---even a short 12 line one--
    can be as useful of a "site" (sorry, too much academic theory in me head)
    for a classroom discussion, and may tell us more about both "poetry"
    and "language" and "the poet" and "the real world" than a huge
    voluminous book---sometimes less is more, macrocosm in the microcosm, etc-
    and sometimes more is less----
    and as Barthes wrote somewhere "rereading is something that goes against
    the ideological and commercial habits of our society" or something to
    that effect (i think in S/z; and maybe certain people would call Barthes
    glib too)..........best, cs.
