My wife read it aloud over breakfast. Basically, if you're a nun,
there's a predictable correlation between the richness of your
linguistic usage and your ability to stave off Alzheimer's. Richness is
defined as "ideas per sentence," with a bias toward maximum density of
ideas.
 
But as I pointed out to her, this does not explain Oppen in the
slightest.
 
All best,
