"By 'letter' I designate that material support that concrete discourse
borrows from language"  --Jacques Lacan
 
I'm haunted by the writing of barred S poets (/ superimposed over S),
 
Poetry of the fading barred S who doesn't die in the sense of Barthes
author-death
but who is subject to the Daddy's constitution as what s/he is not:  I am
another
 
"Fading is not disappearance, but something more haunting:  a presence
that cannot be located and yet cannot be definitely renamed as absence so
that we will cease searching for it" --Tilottama Rajan, _The Supplement
of Reading_.
 
-Peter Jaeger
