Folks,
 
The Electronic Poetry Center now has dozens of audio-art and poetry
soundfiles up for public use.   Everything from Indigenous American song
to digital sound collage.
 
http://writing.upenn.edu/epc/sound
http://writing.upenn.edu/epc/linebreak
 
We have written an extensive information page which describes various
soundfile formats and their use, contains links to free digital audio
player/editor software, and instructions on how to play soundfiles on a
computer *without* a soundcard.
 
EPC soundfile formats include:
.WAV
.AU
.AIFF
.MP2(MPEG)
 
Have a listen.  If you heed help email linebrk@acsu.buffalo.edu.
 
Best,
Martin Spinelli
LINEbreak Producer/Director
