Do previous posts here on writing the body go beyond this quote?
"the body is a permanent contestation of the prerogative
attributed to consciousness of `giving meaning' to each
thing; it lives as this contestation." Emmanuel Levinas,
_Totality & Infinity_, trans. A. Lingis, (Pittsburgh:
Duquesne UP, 1969) 129.
 
tom bell
