From:         Rod Smith <AERIALEDGE@AOL.COM>
Subject:      Cage/Williams/Revill
 
To follow up on a question I asked the list last week:
 
I've recently discovered that the Williams quote on pg 65 of the David Revill
biography of Cage was actually written about George Antheil in 1927. Not
about Cage in 1939 as the book indicates. The actual Williams quote appears
on pg 61 of the _Selected Essays_. Antheil's name, which appears twice in the
Williams paragraph, was somewhere along the lines excised from the paragraph
as it appears in the Cage bio.
 
--Rod
