Walking home from work I was thinking about what moves me
logos?
ethos?
pathos
Aristotle's analysis of tragic poetry
pathos is "when you empathize emotionally via the sympathetic
imagination with represented suffering & its outcome"
and I was thinking about thee, philosophe
with thine own trails of logos-passio
burying Philosophy (same tomb with God)
embracing Poetry (lookout honey he's a Pwoffessah)
and about the po bereft Polis
artificial a collective construct built
by Private Unknown Solderer
no bull cut the bull she said, not maybe a-mused
art hides itself
in Act Five (Hamlet over easy)
and we will talk the sweet nonsense
A*MORE LOCO SENSUS COMUNIS
